sx.blah.discord.util.audio.processors

Class MultiProcessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • sx.blah.discord.util.audio.processors.MultiProcessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAudioProcessor, IAudioProvider

    public class MultiProcessor
extends Object
implements IAudioProcessor
    This is an IAudioProcessor implementation which can combine multiple processors. Note: The higher the processor index, the later the processor is used in the queue.

        public boolean isReady()

      • provide

        public byte[] provide()
        Description copied from interface: IAudioProvider
        This is called to retrieve the actual audio data. This should attempt to return 20 ms of data. The audio must also respect the encoding type returned by IAudioProvider.getAudioEncodingType().
        Specified by:

        Returns:
        The audio data.

      • getChannels

        public int getChannels()
        Description copied from interface: IAudioProvider
        Gets the number of channels in this audio. NOTE: This only matters if IAudioProvider.getAudioEncodingType() does not return IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType.OPUS.
        Specified by:
        getChannels in interface IAudioProvider
        Returns:
        The number of channels. It returns 2 (stereo) by default.

      • getAudioEncodingType

        public IAudioProvider.AudioEncodingType getAudioEncodingType()
        Description copied from interface: IAudioProvider
        This is called to determine the type of audio data provided by this provider. This determines how the audio data is processed.
        Specified by:
        getAudioEncodingType in interface IAudioProvider

      • setProvider
